Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.20,0:00:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say are you all right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.21,0:00:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.96,0:00:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I took some cold medicine that Professor Agasa gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.38,0:00:39.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, your voice sounds awful...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.55,0:00:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should head back so you can look after the house with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.26,0:00:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.35,0:00:51.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the miracle drug this kid took earlier,\Na little cold like that will clear up in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.39,0:00:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it, this "miracle drug"?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.52,0:01:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, it better not be that stuff you brought over\Nwhen we first met you back at the detective office.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.99,0:01:03.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was that Chinese liquor Baigar, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.70,0:01:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.70,0:01:09.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This medicine will be much more\Neffective than something like that alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.58,0:01:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.71,0:01:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, are you sure this is all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.87,0:01:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person we're going to meet wrote in the\Nletter that they had something to tell Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.30,0:01:23.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Won't they be disappointed if we come without Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.55,0:01:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.64,0:01:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They claimed to have found a mistake in the deduction\Nbehind a murder case Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} solved a year ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.23,0:01:33.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And wanted to meet to discuss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.73,0:01:37.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, based on that mistake with his deduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.11,0:01:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They reinvestigated from scratch and are planning\Nto disclose the real truth behind the case to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.86,0:01:45.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I e-mailed Kudo about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.70,0:01:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he'll show as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.14,0:01:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi might?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.70,0:01:56.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why would the letter be sent to your place?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.88,0:02:00.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That might be because I'm Kudo's best buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.85,0:02:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, even if they tried to get in contact with me by letter or phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.44,0:02:06.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person living in my house right now isn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.56,0:02:12.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In frustration, they sent a letter to Hattori, since\Nhe's a high-school detective like me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.85,0:02:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it? The mistake in my deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.80,0:02:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'm not mistaken, the sender was...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.90,0:02:24.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The letter's from Okuda Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, whose address\Nis in East Okuho village on the outskirts of Okuho city.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.07,0:02:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.99,0:02:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.11,0:02:30.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I investigated a murder case that happened in that village...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.41,0:02:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he was the young guy from the village who helped me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.25,0:02:35.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that? Have you caught a cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.33,0:02:42.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, a letter addressed to you was enclosed,\Nso I'll bring it along when I come see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.75,0:02:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can read it properly then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.71,0:02:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, if he's written bad things about your reasoning,\Nthat'll be the perfect thing to make you shake that cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.60,0:02:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only had that one case in East Okuho village, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.65,0:02:58.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A reasoning mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.30,0:03:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That has me worried...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.25,0:03:04.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A desperate crisis...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.01,0:03:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A splendid revival reverses the conclusion to a case!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.20,0:03:09.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Shin'ichi strangely loses his memory...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.31,0:03:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He can no longer assist Heiji with his reasoning abilities!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.33,0:03:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.03,0:03:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.12,0:03:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.35,0:05:01.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.48,0:05:02.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's gone missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.10,0:05:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.40,0:05:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the search request was issued half a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.48,0:05:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was always attracted by the big city...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.11,0:05:18.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The people of the village say he must have left home\Nand found a part-time job or something in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.24,0:05:18.25,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Okuda Makato (19)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.70,0:05:21.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what did you need Okuda Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} for?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.04,0:05:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got a letter from him last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.96,0:05:30.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said when Kudo investigated a murder case that occurred\Nin this village a year ago, he made a mistake in his deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.21,0:05:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to meet and discuss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.67,0:05:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.34,0:05:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I said, he told us to bring Kudo Shin'ichi with...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.06,0:05:44.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.60,0:05:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.73,0:05:50.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you guys friends with that liar!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.98,0:05:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Liar?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.15,0:05:53.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here now, young master.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.85,0:05:54.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.99,0:05:58.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's about that ordeal, go to the village police box.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.91,0:06:02.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have nothing to say to you people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.00,0:06:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, what the hell did that detective kid do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.08,0:06:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, did Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} tell you anything about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.00,0:06:11.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.05,0:06:13.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.17,0:06:17.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that brat said he was heading back to the inn ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.34,0:06:19.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His cold must be getting worse or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.93,0:06:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll head back to the inn as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.39,0:06:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm worried about him being alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.50,0:06:30.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I bet he just didn't want me to go to the crime scene and\Npoint out the mistake in his deduction in front of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.10,0:06:34.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear Kudo Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.00,0:06:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've uncovered proof that you were mistaken in your deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.85,0:06:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to avoid wounding your pride as a detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.20,0:06:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you come see me alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:47.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place will be the mountain hut where you and I first met.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.71,0:06:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Okuda Makoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.80,0:06:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.05,0:06:58.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.71,0:07:04.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cold medicine the professor gave me isn't having any effect all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.93,0:07:08.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that Kudo Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.75,0:07:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's disguising his voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.40,0:07:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.91,0:07:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.49,0:07:21.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.28,0:07:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.87,0:07:22.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.53,0:07:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.87,0:07:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.25,0:07:27.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This cold is hurting my throat and I can't yell...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.45,0:07:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The window...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.99,0:07:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.70,0:07:37.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do I get out of here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.42,0:07:42.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.77,0:07:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.52,0:07:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know where the bottle of\Nmedicine I put in this drawer went to?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.90,0:07:53.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you mean that cold medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.77,0:07:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's what the container said, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.40,0:07:58.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents were a drug that I created.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.11,0:08:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't take one, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.91,0:08:04.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.20,0:08:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.12,0:08:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I can't get out of here quickly...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.63,0:08:18.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A prototype antidote for Apotoxin 4869!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.97,0:08:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.47,0:08:26.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I created it to secretly test on Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}\Nthe next time he came to stay over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.31,0:08:30.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A miracle cure that would restore his body, once\Nreverted to that of a child by Apotoxin 4869...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.69,0:08:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back to that of a high-school student!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.90,0:08:35.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and call him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.02,0:08:38.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he happens to change back to normal in front of the others...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.57,0:08:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tha'll be no joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.01,0:09:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.01,0:09:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} hasn't returned to the inn yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.97,0:09:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and when I asked the people in the village, they said\Nthey saw a boy wearing glasses go into the forest by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.02,0:09:14.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, why don't you just call his cellphone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.31,0:09:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.57,0:09:19.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're out of range here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.48,0:09:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that guy up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.69,0:09:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} even has that terrible cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.86,0:09:25.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That brat's always causing trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.49,0:09:30.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Officer, we'll put off going to the crime scene until later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.66,0:09:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.95,0:09:33.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.25,0:09:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.55,0:09:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.51,0:09:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.90,0:09:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me there was something in that letter addressed\Nto him that asked him to go to some strange location...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.64,0:09:52.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.52,0:09:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.77,0:09:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.89,0:09:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a guy floating stark naked in the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.94,0:09:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I sure did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.61,0:10:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My mom is bringing him a blanket right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.53,0:10:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.03,0:10:06.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't an elementary-school student, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.49,0:10:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.74,0:10:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a young man, probably a high-school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.49,0:10:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A high...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.54,0:10:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A high-school student?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.04,0:10:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.38,0:10:21.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy with the blanket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.40,0:10:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.27,0:10:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.03,0:10:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.07,0:10:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you here, Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.53,0:10:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.49,0:10:54.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.87,0:10:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.26,0:11:11.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of nonsense are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.97,0:11:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the high-school detective of the East, Kudo Shin'ichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.89,0:11:19.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one's going to laugh at a stupid joke like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.19,0:11:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.11,0:11:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.48,0:11:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lost his memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.48,0:11:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.65,0:11:29.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.78,0:11:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or where this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.00,0:11:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.66,0:11:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now that I look closer, isn't this guy that Kudo Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.79,0:11:45.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's so, we shouldn't have bothered rescuing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.34,0:11:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.17,0:11:50.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you lend me something to wear?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.68,0:11:52.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems I'm not wearing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.26,0:11:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.39,0:11:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll lend you my extra set of clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.31,0:11:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, his voice is awfully hoarse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.02,0:12:00.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.56,0:12:02.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.44,0:12:04.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to hurry and find Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.52,0:12:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we don't have to worry about that any—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.66,0:12:13.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, because, the thing is, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.99,0:12:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took a train and went home before us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.50,0:12:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.96,0:12:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That kid told me about it before we went to\Nthe village office, but I completely forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.30,0:12:30.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said it would be bad if his cold got\Nany worse, so he decided to head home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.63,0:12:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, even if he goes back home to the\Ndetective office, there's nobody there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.89,0:12:39.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he mentioned that he'd be staying\Nwith that old man Agasa, or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.02,0:12:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell us that earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.69,0:12:45.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I just tell you I forgot?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:50.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, this location is out of cellphone reception range.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.82,0:12:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we're going to verify where that brat is, we'll have\Nto head back to the inn where they have a land line.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.33,0:13:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since he can't remember anything, we'll have\Nto take this bothersome detective kid with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.67,0:13:05.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You might as well give up trying to return his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.38,0:13:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet he met up with that thing in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.09,0:13:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.05,0:13:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd better hope not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.84,0:13:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.51,0:13:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.93,0:13:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did they mean by the "thing in the forest"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.83,0:13:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji's clothes look pretty good on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.33,0:13:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.58,0:13:44.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} go?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.92,0:13:51.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for Ran, it looks like she's more concerned\Nwith that four-eyed brat than this detective kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.55,0:13:52.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.92,0:13:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You gave him the wrong medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.64,0:14:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't happen to be what that little\Ngirl made at the festival that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.51,0:14:02.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:07.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The antidote for that Apotoxin 4869 that turned Shin'ichi into a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.87,0:14:11.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, that drug will turn\Nhim back into a high-school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.69,0:14:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mistook the drugs that Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} made for cold\Nmedicine and inadvertently gave it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.99,0:14:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't exactly "inadvertent," old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.70,0:14:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More importantly, is it really true that Shin'ichi has lost his memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.87,0:14:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it seems he can't remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.71,0:14:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may be best that he's like that for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.50,0:14:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be easier for him to handle various\Nthings that come up in his original form.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.72,0:14:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.34,0:14:39.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That drug is just a prototype.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.68,0:14:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I may have made a small measurement error...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.76,0:14:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The range of its effectiveness will be 24 hours at most.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.23,0:14:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,24 hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.73,0:14:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't regain his memory before then, it'll turn bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.86,0:14:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.86,0:14:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for his memory, he'll have plenty of time after he shrinks again...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.53,0:14:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of brain-dead things are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.03,0:15:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If someone else with memory loss appears,\Nsomeone's definitely going to discover...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.95,0:15:04.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the two of them are one in the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.20,0:15:06.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.29,0:15:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.37,0:15:11.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that happens, she's going to force him to explain no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.17,0:15:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who forced him to take that sort of drug, and for what reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.88,0:15:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when she knows the truth of what happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.93,0:15:22.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think she can keep it to herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.81,0:15:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, for now, in order to avoid\Nputting her in such a dangerous position...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.44,0:15:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you get him back here before he transforms into a child again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.11,0:15:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, I'll do what I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.65,0:15:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.53,0:15:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.24,0:15:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you whispering?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.37,0:15:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.37,0:15:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, they hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.29,0:15:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems he took some medicine and is\Nsound asleep in bed, so they said not to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.42,0:15:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's good, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.17,0:15:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, let's have dinner and get to sleep early ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.21,0:15:59.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should get back to Beika tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.76,0:16:03.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't we going to hang around here for a couple of days?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.85,0:16:05.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Change of plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.31,0:16:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to get Kudo examined by a doctor soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.23,0:16:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, shouldn't we take Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} along to the crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.11,0:16:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That might help him remember something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.48,0:16:17.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of moronic idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.38,0:16:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, that's a good idea as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.38,0:16:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is nasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.42,0:16:40.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The interior of the house is really messy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.81,0:16:45.44,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The young master insisted that the room\Nbe left as it was at the time of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.06,0:16:45.40,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Shiroyama Kazuma (46)\NPolice Officer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.89,0:16:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young master?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.97,0:16:53.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young master Daiki, who was staying over at a relative's house\Non the night of the incident a year ago, escaped from the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.27,0:16:56.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the brat we met at the village office.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.19,0:17:00.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are these people on either side of him in the photograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.36,0:17:04.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young master Daiki's parents, who both lost their lives in the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.70,0:17:11.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hinohara Takinori san, who was the village\Nmayor at the time, and his wife, Shouko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.29,0:17:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mayor Hinohara was a very easygoing person\Nand was popular with the people in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.21,0:17:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He served as the village mayor for roughly 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.80,0:17:27.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the tragedy from one year ago\Nhas so distressed all those in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.85,0:17:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, these black footprints were from the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.64,0:17:33.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.52,0:17:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminal stabbed the wife in the middle of\Nthe stairs and got her blood on their shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.61,0:17:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The marks here are from them walking around the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.65,0:17:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How awful...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.36,0:17:48.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These footprints go on for quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.16,0:17:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To that veranda, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.92,0:17:57.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a remarkably spacious veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.09,0:18:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bloody footprints turn back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.43,0:18:07.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see why.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.85,0:18:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mayor was forced to fall from here to his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.35,0:18:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the murder weapon found? Or was anything taken?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.60,0:18:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were no bladed weapons found inside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.86,0:18:21.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some jewelry and antiques were found to be missing, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.36,0:18:32.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that remained were the bloody footprints in the room and matching\Nprints making a round trip from the back door to the asphalt roadway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.33,0:18:36.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were those really the only footprints that were found?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.54,0:18:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.58,0:18:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leading up to the day of the incident, it had been\Nraining, which made the ground soft and muddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.05,0:18:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means that, after killing the mayor and his wife, they returned\Nto their car with the murder weapon and the stolen valuables.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must have been a robbery-murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.89,0:18:56.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, who did Kudo say was the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.14,0:19:02.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me he named some innocent\Nperson as the robbery-murder culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.07,0:19:04.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.86,0:19:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Double suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.28,0:19:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This person, Kudo Shin'ichi, deduced that it was a\Nforced double suicide instigated by Mayor Hinohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.25,0:19:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forced double suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.88,0:19:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.51,0:19:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A classmate of Makoto—the boy who was being\Ncared for in this house after his parents passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.43,0:19:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, Makoto is there in the picture too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.81,0:19:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Behind the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.39,0:19:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.89,0:19:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Makoto wouldn't be Okuda Makoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.64,0:19:40.88,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.70,0:19:45.12,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)} Hikawa Moegi (19)\N{\fs12} Makato's Classmate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.12,0:19:45.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Since he was the first to discover the bodies,\NOkuda Makoto was the primary suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.07,0:19:51.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, because he was taking a university entrance exam\Nand was staying at a city hotel at the time of the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.99,0:19:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was instantly cleared of suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.58,0:19:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, let me ask you this: Where is Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.37,0:20:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite sending a letter stating he had discovered a mistake in\NKudo's deduction and even after telling us to bring him here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.09,0:20:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are they still saying that he's gone missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.55,0:20:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not that he's gone missing...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.39,0:20:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Makoto has probably been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.01,0:20:16.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.14,0:20:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.56,0:20:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The villagers are saying that Makoto is\Nworking part-time jobs in the city, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.69,0:20:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inheritance he received as an adopted\Nchild of this family was considerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.90,0:20:29.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're saying someone killed him in order\Nto get their hands on the inheritance money?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.15,0:20:31.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.07,0:20:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that somehow weren't the case, there's no way\NI wouldn't have heard from Makoto for half a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.58,0:20:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the one who killed him was probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.04,0:20:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.45,0:20:42.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The forest"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.75,0:20:49.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, who sent me that letter, and for what reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.72,0:20:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, what was the mistake in Kudo's deduction?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.18,0:20:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The motive behind Mayor Hinohara's forced double suicide was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.64,0:21:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The desperation he felt after his\Ndoctor diagnosed him with cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.19,0:21:06.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what Kudo kun said a year ago,\Nbut the real situation poses a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.57,0:21:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.71,0:21:10.91,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm a reporter for the Touto Shinbun, Kawauchi Misato.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.95,0:21:15.33,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Kawauchi Misato (36)\N{\fs12} Newspaper Reporter
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.05,0:21:15.03,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but the door was open, so I came on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.41,0:21:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what was the problem in that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.99,0:21:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later, a nurse at the hospital let slip some information to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.08,0:21:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was cancer, but the tumor was benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.04,0:21:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mayor had been pleased to hear it\Ncould be completely resolved via surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.84,0:21:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.47,0:21:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kudo, what does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Explain yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.64,0:21:37.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I'm talking to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.97,0:21:39.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.39,0:21:40.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.18,0:21:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.73,0:21:44.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudo...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.98,0:21:51.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.57,0:21:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finally get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.28,0:21:57.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the people in this village hate this detective kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.57,0:21:58.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.74,0:22:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the dreadful person who sullied\Nthe name of everyone's beloved mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.08,0:22:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's frightening...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.54,0:22:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, doesn't that mean the real\Ncriminal is still around here somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.17,0:22:15.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rumor among the villagers is that it was\Ndone by the thing that lives in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.93,0:22:19.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I heard someone else mention that earlier—what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.35,0:22:21.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it that lives in the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.27,0:22:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a legend that's been handed down in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.69,0:22:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Legend?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.19,0:22:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard it many times since I was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.31,0:22:31.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you encounter him in the forest, don't look in his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.19,0:22:36.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you do, you'll be cursed...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.95,0:22:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you'll be enslaved by the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.58,0:22:43.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sh-Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.13,0:22:49.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.21,0:22:53.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing, I just had a strange feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.02,0:23:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't that just some ordinary folklore tale?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.15,0:23:15.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that the story of the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.86,0:23:23.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A legend that's been handed down in this area about a local\Nguardian deity who punishes those who lay waste to the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.49,0:23:28.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nine years ago, at this lake, a young woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.79,0:23:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lost her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.59,0:23:33.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.55,0:23:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there really something in the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.30,0:23:37.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.97,0:23:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That girl went into the forest and never came home...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.26,0:23:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And on the evening of the third day that\Nthe entire village spent looking for her...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.93,0:23:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The exhausted villagers started spreading a rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.10,0:23:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had defied the ancient law.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.77,0:23:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By venturing into the forest on a dark night, the girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.23,0:23:59.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roused the anger of the guardian of the forest, the\NShiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, and received her punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.49,0:24:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.62,0:24:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the girl's father heard the rumor...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.70,0:24:10.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He shook off those who tried to stop him, and\Nran into the forest as the day drew to a close.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.04,0:24:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was to never be seen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.67,0:24:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two days passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.84,0:24:18.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone who was walking in the forest lost their\Nfooting, fell into the lake, and nearly drowned...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.84,0:24:21.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they found the girl's body there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.05,0:24:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, I think her name was Okuda Tamako.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.31,0:24:28.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okuda?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.06,0:24:29.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.52,0:24:33.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was the little sister of Okuda Makoto, who sent you that letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.65,0:24:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the father who went into the forest to search...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.90,0:24:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that was Makoto's father.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.82,0:24:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He has never been found.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.86,0:24:46.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be that the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} got Makoto's father as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.87,0:24:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, come on, there's no reason to decide some fictional thing did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.84,0:24:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't believe it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.38,0:24:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.17,0:25:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.97,0:25:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Up in a tree, dyed crimson by the evening sun,\Nsitting silently, sneering, baring its teeth...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.10,0:25:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That white-haired monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.93,0:25:11.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.27,0:25:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't you have just mistaken a monkey or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.65,0:25:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a monkey!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.48,0:25:20.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A person from the town hall saw it last week also!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.19,0:25:21.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, isn't that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.32,0:25:27.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would that creature need to kill the mayor and his wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.87,0:25:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did they go into the forest at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.87,0:25:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The village redevelopment.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.00,0:25:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mayor Hinohara was planning to build\Na large tourist facility in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.79,0:25:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.30,0:25:42.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how he earned the wrath of the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.34,0:25:45.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, and thanks to that, the plans were withdrawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.84,0:25:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's despite the plans being proposed by the village hero, Mayor\NHinohara, in order to counter the continuing village depopulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.10,0:25:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.40,0:25:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What, you didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.94,0:26:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he was young, he was an athlete who was even nominated to\Nbe the Japanese representative in track and field at the Olympics.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.95,0:26:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't remember which event it was though.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.99,0:26:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're interested, why don't you go check?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.78,0:26:11.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look in his room on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.00,0:26:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.54,0:26:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like he took the championship in several events.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.50,0:26:20.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they don't say which events they were, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.69,0:26:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are only the medals here?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.30,0:26:27.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he remove the ribbons?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.18,0:26:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.47,0:26:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A statue of Niou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.14,0:26:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.93,0:26:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's pretty heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.77,0:26:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was really well made, with lots of intricate detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.15,0:26:40.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, where's the other one?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.82,0:26:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you talk about Niou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} (two kings),\Nthere should be a pair of guardian kings.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.20,0:26:48.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one with its mouth closed is Unzou.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.95,0:26:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usually Azou, with his mouth open, is placed alongside.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.83,0:26:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the night of the incident a year ago, the Azou Niou...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.62,0:27:00.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Disappeared from this house along with the wife's jewelry.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.17,0:27:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so the culprit must have taken it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.38,0:27:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, were they expensive?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.38,0:27:07.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.34,0:27:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're the work of a famous sculptor from the Edo period—\Nnowadays, neither would go for under five million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.27,0:27:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Five million!?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.39,0:27:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, isn't that odd?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.94,0:27:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would they only take one?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.56,0:27:22.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't they be worth more if they were together?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.11,0:27:27.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. However, he was concerned about this point as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.74,0:27:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who came to this crime scene a year ago, Kudo Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.74,0:27:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Kudo, are you sure you can't remember anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.46,0:27:38.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Hey, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.67,0:27:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.34,0:27:45.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.26,0:27:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.67,0:27:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come and see this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.63,0:27:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.43,0:27:57.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A picture of Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.31,0:28:03.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the photograph from the first time\NShin'ichi was covered in a magazine...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.27,0:28:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How nostalgic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.07,0:28:07.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They had it enlarged.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.28,0:28:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, that's really huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.78,0:28:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are files here on all of the cases that Shin'ichi has solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.16,0:28:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whose room is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.08,0:28:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Makoto's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.29,0:28:23.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Makoto really worshipped this high-school\Ndetective Kudo Shin'ichi here, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.17,0:28:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why, when he heard that Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was to join\Nthe investigation into this case, Makoto was ecstatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.01,0:28:32.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he was sure he'd catch the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.39,0:28:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the conclusion this guy came up with was that\Nthe mayor instigated a forced double suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.31,0:28:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you might expect, Makoto was devastated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.35,0:28:43.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd lost his mother to an illness when he was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.31,0:28:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when Makoto was left orphaned, Mayor\NHinohara was the one who adopted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.45,0:28:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were a typical type-0 family - Mayor Hinohara, his\Nwife, and young master Daiki were all very generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.49,0:29:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He always said he was very fortunate to be made to feel so at-home.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.04,0:29:06.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he couldn't believe the\Nmayor would ever lay a hand on his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.63,0:29:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, he told himself time and time again that he had to accept it...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.26,0:29:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Makoto still believed that you were a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.84,0:29:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, it's been proven that the great detective was\Nincorrect in his presentation of the true facts behind the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.68,0:29:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His, conclusion that Mayor Hinohara's motive for murder was his\Ndesperation after his doctor told him he had cancer was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.19,0:29:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, and Makoto tried to contact you\Nmultiple times through letters and phone calls...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.99,0:29:39.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was worried that he couldn't get a hold of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.20,0:29:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he went to visit and ask you to\Nreinvestigate directly, but you weren't home!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.57,0:29:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.11,0:29:47.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd been shrunk and wasn't home.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.00,0:29:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now that you're here, you've lost your memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.09,0:29:52.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you playing at?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.67,0:29:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.76,0:30:00.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you leave me alone in this room for a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.56,0:30:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a feeling that I might remember something.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.48,0:30:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's so...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.94,0:30:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll leave you alone for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.69,0:30:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take your time and recall what you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.37,0:30:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're taking care of the mayor's son,\NDaiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, at your house now, Shiroyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.71,0:30:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, and Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} as well until half a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.26,0:30:36.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, there was something bothering me earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.76,0:30:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is he still called Okuda Makoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.10,0:30:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Mayor Hinohara adopted him, should\Nhe not be called Hinohara Makoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.11,0:30:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.23,0:30:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how he's referred to in the family registry, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.65,0:30:51.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said it would be presumptuous to call\Nhimself by the mayor's family name.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.52,0:30:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Makoto always used his former name, Okuda.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.82,0:30:57.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.36,0:30:59.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Did you remember anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.24,0:31:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, don't lose heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.91,0:31:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you'll get your memory back eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.09,0:31:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was wondering what kind of ploy you'd come up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.30,0:31:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it seems that you haven't thought of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.26,0:31:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ploy?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.43,0:31:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know all about it, Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. About your ulterior motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.19,0:31:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh, what's with that face?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.90,0:31:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you think I hadn't found you out?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.86,0:31:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if you come around and want to confess it all to me,\Ncome and see me at the Kotou Inn where I'm staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.99,0:31:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you do, I can write more favorably about you in my article...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.54,0:31:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the truth that you've tried to keep\Nhidden—the truth that must not be said.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.93,0:32:02.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can never tell anyone about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.55,0:32:06.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth that must not be said.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.56,0:32:12.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What an unpleasant old lady that newspaper reporter is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.65,0:32:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it? Kudo's ulterior motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.48,0:32:21.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, what we know now is, no matter how we look at it, the\Nincident couldn't have been anything other than a robbery-murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.41,0:32:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this detective kid deduced it was a forced double suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.20,0:32:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And missed the mark on the motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.91,0:32:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's one more problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.79,0:32:36.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this forest, something of an unknown nature is lurking even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.67,0:32:39.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.01,0:32:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, and this is just speaking hypothetically, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.39,0:32:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.43,0:32:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If someone you liked suddenly reappeared after\Nyou've waited so long, but had lost their memory...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.60,0:32:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were you, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, what would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.87,0:32:57.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.86,0:33:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd be crying like mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.74,0:33:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The joy of seeing him after so long and the sadness over his\Nforgetting all about himself would come welling up together.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.99,0:33:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you didn't feel that strongly about it, it wouldn't be\Nsomeone you love, but maybe just a normal friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.17,0:33:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.88,0:33:20.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no! What I just said was for someone stupid like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.47,0:33:22.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't feel anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.89,0:33:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.09,0:33:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just feel like Shin'ichi is as far away as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.77,0:33:31.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.31,0:33:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he gets his memory back, everything will be back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.70,0:33:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.45,0:33:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.87,0:33:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's started raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.58,0:33:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.12,0:33:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's run to the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.50,0:33:54.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.93,0:34:07.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s not in his room?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.97,0:34:11.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I got up early and his futon was left empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.35,0:34:12.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.56,0:34:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.94,0:34:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just asked the people from the village, and they said they saw\Nhim go into Mayor Hinohara's house early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.90,0:34:22.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.86,0:34:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His memory has returned?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.95,0:34:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.91,0:34:37.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudo's shoes and a woman's shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.88,0:34:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you here? Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.09,0:34:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.59,0:34:44.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did your memory come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.68,0:34:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.68,0:34:48.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Kudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.31,0:34:54.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.52,0:34:55.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.98,0:34:57.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's so much blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.53,0:35:08.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.16,0:35:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.53,0:35:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.37,0:35:14.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.66,0:35:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I fell unconscious...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.83,0:35:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when I came to, I was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.80,0:35:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it me?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.97,0:35:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.26,0:35:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did I do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.80,0:35:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This lady's still breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.97,0:35:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, so this is where you went, detective kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.65,0:35:43.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the newspaper reporter!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.94,0:35:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.65,0:35:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's blood everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.40,0:35:48.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll look for explanations later!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.03,0:35:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and call for an ambulance and the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.78,0:35:53.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.16,0:35:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's best if you just call the ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.87,0:35:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.91,0:35:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This lady's wound...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.25,0:35:59.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't someone do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.67,0:36:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you tell by looking?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.71,0:36:05.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we call the police with the situation as it is,\NKudo-covered in blood-will be made the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.96,0:36:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.13,0:36:09.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.13,0:36:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.34,0:36:13.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way Kudo would stab someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.72,0:36:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been framed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.39,0:36:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone tried to make it look like Kudo did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.52,0:36:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems there are plenty of people in this\Nvillage who bear a grudge against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.55,0:36:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More importantly, if Kudo is taken in by the police now...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.78,0:36:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how innocent he is, there will be\Na lengthy investigation and this'll go bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.11,0:36:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a possibility that the drug returned\NKudo to his normal state will wear off then.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.83,0:36:39.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, Kazuha, call the ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.12,0:36:41.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle, you bring the car over here and we'll hide Kudo in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.54,0:36:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.50,0:36:44.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.55,0:36:47.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An ambulance siren...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.13,0:36:48.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.76,0:36:51.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the sound of a patrol car, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.30,0:36:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're getting closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.89,0:36:54.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could have called them?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.10,0:37:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.98,0:37:07.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You all had questions about how the murder\Ncase that occurred here a year ago was settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.73,0:37:12.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, despite having visited this place last\Nnight, you came here again this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.49,0:37:18.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when you discovered the newspaper reporter, Kawauchi\NMisato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had been stabbed in the abdomen, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.04,0:37:21.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Famous detective Mouri Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.75,0:37:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.42,0:37:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? When you got here, there really was\Nno one else here except the victim, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.96,0:37:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.26,0:37:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.47,0:37:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.47,0:37:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, they left the murder weapon, and once we check the "gesokon"\Nin the entryway, we'll know who the culprit was soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.98,0:37:42.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Gesokon"?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.27,0:37:44.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a police term for footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.48,0:37:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how will you know from that?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.36,0:37:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were left behind in the muddy\Nground due to the rain that fell last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.91,0:37:58.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both the victim's and the culprit's footprints are deep and distinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.66,0:38:02.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Detective, those may have been our footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.58,0:38:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, when you came here, the sun had\Ncome up and the ground was fairly dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.42,0:38:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your footprints are shallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.88,0:38:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We will know when we compare them\Nwith your shoes that are in the entryway.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.88,0:38:19.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What bothers me are the footprints left by the culprit when they\Ncame here while the ground was still muddy this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.97,0:38:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did they leave out the back of the\Nhouse after the ground had dried?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.35,0:38:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Considering the tracks coming after the ground had dried, there\Nshould be four people here, but there only seem to be three.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.40,0:38:38.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, for some reason, the footprints\Nof the 4th person leave from the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.12,0:38:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Sleeping Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} can solve this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.50,0:38:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.04,0:38:46.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.58,0:38:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, Kudo? I know it's a little tight, but be patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.54,0:38:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as I find the real criminal,\Nyou can get out, but you need to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.87,0:39:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That little girl said the medicine would only\Nremain effective for approximately 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.66,0:39:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I definitely have to settle this case before night falls without fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.90,0:39:10.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.15,0:39:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to lie anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.65,0:39:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's right, Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.65,0:39:19.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be better to tell the police the truth\Nlike we should and help them investigate?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.72,0:39:21.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These two don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.74,0:39:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we're in a pretty bad situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.71,0:39:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that, before the police came, the only\Nones who went to the house were the four of us...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.13,0:39:36.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along with the victim, Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and that detective kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.72,0:39:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that really true?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.13,0:39:39.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.47,0:39:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They searched the perimeter of the house carefully...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.88,0:39:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But only the footprints from we six were found.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.73,0:39:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, you bought Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s shoes\Nlast night at a store in the village, Heiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.65,0:39:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how well you are able to hide\Nhim, won't they figure it out soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.44,0:39:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.24,0:39:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone asked the two of them to come to that house...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.16,0:40:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put Kudo to sleep with some sort of drug, put on his\Nclothes, and stabbed Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in the stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.87,0:40:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you know, if that's what happened, that someone's\Nfootprints should have been left there too, shouldn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.71,0:40:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I said it was a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.75,0:40:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What method could they have used?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.72,0:40:19.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.05,0:40:23.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since that house should have been locked, how did the culprit get in?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.80,0:40:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither Kudo nor Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had the key on them, did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.56,0:40:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.93,0:40:33.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we went last night, that policeman, Shiroyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, opened it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.36,0:40:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.32,0:40:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would Shiroyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} have the key to that house?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.23,0:40:39.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young master Daiki entrusted it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.70,0:40:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, does anyone other than you have a key to that house?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.87,0:40:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the keys from the former owners of\Nthe house, Mayor Hinohara and his wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.12,0:40:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have custody of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.38,0:41:00.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If anyone else has one, it would only be the adopted\Nson of the household, Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, who's gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.51,0:41:06.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, come to think of it, while Makoto kun was off\Nin the city taking his university entrance exams...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.72,0:41:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who was helping with the chores at the Hinohara house,\Nhis classmate Hikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was temporarily given a key as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.23,0:41:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, the incident occurred on the day\Nthat Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was taking his university exam, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.99,0:41:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.41,0:41:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as that goes, that girl, Hikawa, could be suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.37,0:41:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, when she was entrusted with the key,\Nshe could have had a duplicate made.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.00,0:41:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In both the case where Kudo made his deduction mistake\Nand in the incident today, could it have been that girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.42,0:41:41.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what was his deduction mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.09,0:41:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Certainly enough the inside of that house was completely trashed...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.09,0:41:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But according to Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s deduction,\Nafter Mayor Hinohara killed his wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.56,0:41:53.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have done that himself to\Nmake it look like a robbery-murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.69,0:41:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot—it seems that, like today, at the time of the incident\Na year ago, the ground was muddy from the rain, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.32,0:42:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike this time, there was only one set of footprints around the\Nhouse making a round trip from the back door to the roadway.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.24,0:42:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit had walked around inside the house wearing their shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.49,0:42:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Mayor Hinohara was planning to make it look like a robbery...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.17,0:42:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he left the house wearing those shoes and\Nthen returned to the house still wearing them...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.21,0:42:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't those shoes be somewhere in the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.71,0:42:23.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.17,0:42:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had thrown the shoes outside the house,\Nthe police would have discovered them already.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.30,0:42:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the distance from the veranda of the house to the\Nlake is around 30 meters, he couldn't have reached it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.64,0:42:39.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, wouldn't Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} have realized all of that also?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.02,0:42:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's what I've been thinking about since last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.07,0:42:44.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no-no-no-no!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.90,0:42:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should be thinking about the case today, not the one a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.24,0:42:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the culprit had a key and ambushed them in that house...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.37,0:42:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would have been impossible for the culprit to have gone\Nin and out of that house without leaving footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.58,0:42:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An impossible crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.86,0:43:00.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An impossible crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.44,0:43:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A baffling murder trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.11,0:43:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.82,0:43:06.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.74,0:43:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were Shin'ichi, I'm sure he'd...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.26,0:43:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.60,0:43:16.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only Kudo were in his right mind, we could\Ncombine wits and have the answer in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.52,0:43:19.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have really encountered the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.23,0:43:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this have to do with the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.48,0:43:25.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's what the people from the village said yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.74,0:43:29.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He lost his memory because he met the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.74,0:43:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And last night before we went to sleep,\NRan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and I asked someone at the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.20,0:43:38.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked what we should do if someone\Nhad been cursed by the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.63,0:43:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they said...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.04,0:43:43.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go into the forest while the sun still shines.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.13,0:43:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you see the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r},\Ncall out to him at the top of your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.63,0:43:53.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you continue praying to him with a clear and unclouded heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.22,0:43:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His curse will be lifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.81,0:44:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although, basically no one has ever put that to an actual test.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.69,0:44:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the person at the inn said that\Nlady newspaper reporter had done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.65,0:44:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.03,0:44:07.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.65,0:44:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said that a year ago, when she came to\Ncollect information about the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.03,0:44:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She brought her daughter along and the\Ngirl went into the forest to not return.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.12,0:44:17.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.71,0:44:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.37,0:44:21.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.33,0:44:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She took what we were just saying\Nseriously and went off into the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.20,0:44:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.58,0:44:35.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.48,0:44:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I beg you, please restore Shin'ichi to the way he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.54,0:44:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my clouded heart is good enough, I'll give it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.76,0:44:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.76,0:44:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Make him the real Shin'ichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.51,0:44:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.53,0:45:09.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found him...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.20,0:45:13.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I actually found him...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.68,0:45:17.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.08,0:45:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no use... I'm too frightened to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.49,0:45:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.24,0:45:32.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.07,0:45:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.52,0:45:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no good...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.82,0:45:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My body hurts all over and I can't move
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.53,0:45:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What in the world have I done?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.07,0:45:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rushing of into to forest and then carelessly falling...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.62,0:45:58.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.72,0:46:18.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.10,0:46:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.69,0:46:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.61,0:46:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Make Shin'ichi the way he was...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.35,0:48:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.23,0:48:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's completely covered with pictures and articles of that detective kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.98,0:48:10.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.15,0:48:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My wounds have been dressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.65,0:48:14.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who on earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.23,0:48:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's blood is on his clothes and his\Nfingerprints are on the murder weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.86,0:48:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how you look at it, he has to be the culprit, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.12,0:48:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.79,0:48:26.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy is the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.08,0:48:37.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.28,0:48:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s Curse
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.02,0:48:44.89,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look forward to the next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.06,0:48:41.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, we'll resolve Shin'ichi's memory!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.52,0:48:42.82,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And the truth behind the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.83,0:48:44.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Please look forward to it!
